OL,7,FThe report from the nine-member
OL,8,Fcommittee, which scrutinises the work
OL,9,Fof Britain's intelligence agencies,
OL,10,Fonly covers the period up to August
OL,11,F2023 with publication delayed due to
OL,12,Flast year's election.
OL,14,FBetween the beginning of 2022 and the
OL,15,Fend of the committee's evidence-
OL,16,Fgathering in August 2023, the report
OL,17,Ffound there had been at least 15
OL,18,Fattempts at murder or kidnap against
OL,19,FBritish nationals or UK residents.
