OL,7,FThe UK had sanctioned 508 individuals
OL,8,Fand 1,189 individuals relating to Iran
OL,9,Fby August 2023, but the committee
OL,10,Furged the government to reconsider
OL,11,Fwhether sanctions "will in practice
OL,12,Fdeliver behavioural change or in fact
OL,13,Funhelpfully push Iran towards China".
OL,15,FHowever, it welcomed the decision to
OL,16,Fplace Iran in the "enhanced tier" of
OL,17,Fthe new Foreign Influence Registration
OL,18,FScheme, placing extra burdens on
OL,19,Fpeople acting on Tehran's behalf in
OL,20,Fthe UK.
